      "raw_text": "The Great Northern was tied up\nfrom O'Clock yesterday morning\nuntil midnight by the derailing of\nIs cars of a west bound freight\ntrain at Edwald, Wash. A wrecker\nfrom Hillyard worked II hours be-\nfore clearing the track. No one was\ninjured. A shoo-fly track was\nbuilt around the place where the\nold one is torn up for more than\n1900 feet."
    }
